### Run the Summarize workflow (uses the AI agent as a workflow step)
POST http://localhost:7071/api/workflows/Summarize/run
Content-Type: text/plain

The speed of light in vacuum is approximately 299,792,458 meters per second. It is denoted by the letter c and is a fundamental physical constant. Einstein's theory of special relativity established that nothing can travel faster than light. This speed limit has profound implications for our understanding of space, time, and causality.
